properties.title: Painted Ladies at Alamo Square 2011_1
properties.description: nxtrFOTO posted a photo: I joined a small photo group tour on this day and we walked around the Mission District of San Francisco, California from 8:30 AM to 5:30 PM, shooting beautiful and colorful murals, works of art. It was a fantastic experience and I'll be uploading some of my mural captures soon. After the shoot, I picked up my friend Macneil and we drove around San Francisco looking for interesting things to shoot. It's never happened before but we found parking almost immediately at each chosen place; North Beach, Alamo Sqaure, and Hayes Valley. It must have been our lucky parking night! I've taken pictures of the Painted Ladies from Alamo Sqaure before so I wanted this shot to be a little different. Just a little! I walked all over the park looking for a different vantage point while under pressure from the rapidly changing light. I settled on this point of view because it included City Hall and part of the Bay Bridge in the background, just slightly different from my previous shots here. Thanks for stopping by and having a look, and as always, I appreciate your comments, faves and views.View large in lightbox.Copyright ©2011 - C. properties.title: Dolores Tennis
properties.description: mike dillon posted a photo: 365 Project Day 182: July 1, 2011 Yup, another one of those sunlight/glare/shadow shots I've been so fond of lately... I took a walk down to the Mission this evening, partly because I just wanted to take a walk, and partly because I had my heart set on some delicious, cheap cherries from one of the Mission markets. On the way down, I stopped by Dolores Park for a bit. The park was packed, due to the lovely weather, and the low evening sun made for some interesting light. In the end, this turned out to be my favorite shot from the walk. Unfortunately, I couldn't find any cherries. :(

properties.title: Docks and Piers
properties.description: sibbiblue posted a photo: Description I have been experimenting with this view quite a while. On my harddrive I have different exposures, different angles, different filter settings of almost the same subject. They all have their unique and special look. After reviewing almost any combination or any image, I decided to like this one best. It is always a real pleasure to get up really early in San Francisco and walk down to the piers. Almost nobody is out there except some crazy fishermen hunting for an early catch. From time to time you get into some nice small talk with one of them. There was a street light which lit the wooden poles in the foreground. Fancy look!Technique: f/11 t: 8,0sec ISO: 100focal length: 25mm on a Nikon D7000 (APS-C) I used a darker exposure and hand blended it for better highlight recovery. Noise reduction by NIK software Dfine 2.0 (trial version), btw. excellent result(!), minor contrast and color corrections, dodge and burn using luminosity masks, a final touch in Lightroom again in order to get a good proof for web display.Postprocessing: Lightroom LR 3.3 and Phostoshop CS4TUMBLR or follow me on TWITTER Recently I also show some of my flickr images at 500px
